==Old English==
===Etymology===
Germanic ''*ausō'', from Indo-European ''*h₂ous-''.

''Germanic cognates:'' Old Frisian [[are|āre]], Old Saxon [[ora|ōra]] (Dutch [[oor]]), Old High German [[ora|ōra]] (German [[Ohr]]), Old Norse [[eyra]] (Swedish [[öra]]), Gothic [[𐌰𐌿𐍃𐍉]].

''Indo-European cognates:'' Greek [[οὖς]], Latin [[auris]], Old Church Slavonic [[оухо]] (Russian [[ухо]]), Old Irish [[au]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /æ:aɹe/

===Noun===
'''ēare''' ''n''
# the [[ear]]

